
                                            Police are trying to determine the identity of the victim and the circumstances surrounding the murder.
                                         CAPE TOWN - Police officers are combing an area in Delft where a body was discovered in a grave.  Officers were called out to a bushy area along Symphony Way on Wednesday morning.  Someone had found a hand sticking out from a grave. Police are trying to determine the identity of the victim and the circumstances surrounding the murder.  The police's Frederick van Wyk said: “We’ll also prove whether the body is not that of a 14-year-old teenager who was reported missing on Tuesday night by a family member. At that time, we immediately launched a search. The investigation continues.”